# Optional: Google Tag Manager container ID (loads one script; configure GA4, Ads, Clarity, etc. inside GTM).
# Netlify: set PUBLIC_GTM_CONTAINER_ID or GTM_CONTAINER_ID to GTM-XXXXXXX, then redeploy (static HTML is built at deploy time).
# If Netlify env is unreliable, set `gtmContainerId` in src/data/site.ts instead (env overrides when non-empty).
# PUBLIC_GTM_CONTAINER_ID=GTM-XXXXXXX

# Production site URL (canonical, Open Graph, JSON-LD). Set in Netlify to your live domain, e.g. https://www.sagehomeimprove.com
# PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.sagehomeimprove.com
